msgstr ""

#: src/view/06_control_flow.md:242
msgid ""
"This strong typing is very powerful, because it enables all sorts of compile-"
"time optimizations. But it can be a little annoying in conditional logic "
"like this, because you can’t return different types from different branches "
"of a condition in Rust. There are two ways to get yourself out of this "
"situation:"
